# REQUIREMENT ID CONVENTIONS
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

| Category | Prefix | Example |
|----------|--------|---------|
| Architecture | CA-ARCH | CA-ARCH-001 |
| Rule Pack | CA-RP | CA-RP-001 |
| Swarm | CA-SWARM | CA-SWARM-001 |
| Validation | CA-VAL | CA-VAL-001 |
| Regulatory | CA-REG | CA-REG-001 |

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# RULE PACK CATEGORIES (Authoritative)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

These rule pack categories are authoritative:

| Category | Purpose | Example Agents |
|----------|---------|----------------|
| Domain | Business logic rules | TB-Review, Arabic-AP |
| Technical | Implementation standards | Code-Style, Schema-Valid |
| Compliance | Regulatory requirements | GDPR-Check, AI-Act |
| Operations | Runtime behavior | Monitoring, Alerting |
| Governance | Process controls | Approval-Flow, Audit-Trail |

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# DRIFT DETECTION COMMANDS
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

```bash
# Full audit for clinerules-agents domain
make audit-spec-drift-domain DOMAIN=clinerules-agents

# List all .clinerules files
find . -name ".clinerules*" -type f

# Verify rule pack consistency
grep -r "## Purpose" docs/latex/specs/*/. 2>/dev/null | grep clinerules
```

